cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper presents a methodology for training Spiking Deep Networks for object recognition problems using biologically realistic neurons. This falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on object recognition, which is a subfield of Computer Vision (cs.CV). The methodology involves unsupervised learning using the Auto-Encoder model, which is a popular technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces sparsity in the feature representations, which is a common theme in Systems and Control (cs.SY). Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SY, in that order.
